Clone
  - Definition: It is a copy of a repository on your local machine
  - Purpose: To have a local version to work on
  - Upstream changes: Can pull changes directly from the original repository
  - Contribution: Directly push to the original repository if you have write permissions

Fork
  - Definition: It is a copy of a repository on a hosting service (Ex: GitHub, etc.)
  - Purpose: To have a own version to make changes without affeting the original project
  - Upstream changes: Can sunc with original repo, but requires setting up an upstream remote & pull changes
  - Contribution: Make changes in your fork & then submit a PR to the original repo
